args:
The fight to quell the demons' rampage begins.
As the Halidom's heroes join with other brave
souls to drive back the Five Archdemons,
Sandalphon attacks the demonic entities and
Harle seals Loki away. Once all this is done,
there is but a single foe remaining...
It's time. Regina, use your tablet\nto give the signal.
To all who have gathered under our banner\nthis day, know that you have my deepest\nthanks and admiration.

We fight to defend this world from a great
evil, and I trust that each of you has
something precious they wish to protect.
I know that I do...
So while the shape of our desires may\ndiffer, their essence is the same. Now let\nus join forces and see the deed done!
All units, prepare to attack! We march with\nthe armies of Chanzelia and New Alberia\nto crush the demons beneath our boots!
Steel yourselves, my brothers and sisters!
Ooo... So many eager little toys!
You face more than humans this day.
Wait, dragons too? Hot damn, baby!\nIt's the Empyrean War all over again.
Now come closer so I can grind you all\nto paste between my teeth.
Show the enemy a hell deeper than any\ndemon has yet known! Use every ounce of\nyour strength to bleed their will to fight!
By the authority of my law,\nI sentence you all to die.
Hie, warriors of the Sandreach!\nAbandon these vile blackguards\nto the midden!
Send the injured to me for treatment!
Thanks to you, I can get back out there.\nNow let's show 'em we won't go down\nwithout a fight!

It seems even demons are powerless
before the overwhelming might of
King Xander and his loyal vassals!
Ha HA! Ha ha ha ha ha!
Hubris can be fatal, Xander. But still,\nwe've stopped the flow of energy back\nto Satan. That should mean...
By the Goddess! The miasma is thinning!
Stage one of the operation is a success.
Those are the fiends that entered Grams. \nThey certainly are a great host...
Soldiers of the Watch! Join with your\nbold companions in the knighthood\nand eliminate that horde of fiends!
You have my thanks, friends. We shall use\nthis chance to strike Satan down.
Goodness me, you actually cleared the\nDemonlord's miasma! I may have to\nrevise my opinion of you people...
The quickest path to the north where\nSatan awaits is through this cathedral.
I sense an evil presence nearby...\nStand ready!
Looks like it's the demonic entities.
There are too many, and we cannot afford\nto tarry here overlong.
Then shall we release our Sigils now?
You must conserve your strength.\nThis fight is mine alone.
Hurry to your sister's side, Regina.\nWith the power of our new Sigil,\nI can handle this many myself.
Let the will of the Goddess\nbe made manifest.
She just cleaved through dozens of them\nwith a single attack!
That's a real good look for ol' Sandalphon.\nWhatcha say, Ramiel? Can you do that?

Releasing one's heavenly wings is no
mean feat, and she has known the method
all along. It will take time for the rest of
us to reach that state.

We're more liable to hurt ourselves than
the enemy if we attempt to use them now.
But once I master the technique, I will be
more than happy to show it to you.
I'm gonna hold you to that.
Enough idle words. Go, Regina.\nSee your sister released.
He's not moving at all, which means he's\nstill recovering his energy.
Then let us retrieve the Sacred Shard\nbefore he wakes. ...Nnngh?!

Welcome to the soulbinding sigil I
prepared especially for you! Oh, and
there's no way to escape it, juuuust
in case you were wondering.
It has been some time, my false prince.\nAnd what a delightful surprise to see the\nangels and their apostles again!
Loki! You're the demon who stole\nHarle's identity!
Yes, and I must say you surprised me!\nThe angels revived? The supply of energy\nto my lord halted? Excellently done.
But did you ever stop to wonder why I\nnever once stepped foot beyond the\ncurtain of miasma?
Don't tell me you expected us\nto make it through?!
You make it sound as if I have more faith\nin you than you do. It's no simple thing,\nthis spell, but the effort clearly paid off.
And now here you are, doomed to watch\nthe world's end from a short step away.\nHow deliciously humiliating!
I think I've earned some entertainment\nafter all of this, so let's see those faces\ncontort in impotent despair!
You'll get no satisfaction from us, demon!
Fiery to the last! But your pathetic barking\nis wasted. Nothing will change, I'm afraid.
I wouldn't be so sure about that.

Satan was sealed by Metatron's power.
The Five Archdemons by mimicries.
But you, Loki? You were a different
matter altogether.

This curiosity got me to thinking,
so I did a bit of research and found a
long-lost sealing spell designed JUST
to take care of little old you.
Alberian Capital Guard Chief Harle,\nreporting only slightly belatedly for duty.\nDo forgive my tardiness, Your Highness.
I simply knew it would be impossible to\nprove my identity unless my impostor was\nstanding right in front of you.
So you've just been sneaking around\nand waiting this entire time?!
In his defense, the man DID choose\na good moment to appear.

This allowed me to approach Loki without
detectionand now the demon will sup
upon the very same humiliation he once
inflicted upon me.
Oh, but I can. I very, VERY much can.\nI do hope you enjoy wandering the space\nbetween worlds for all eternity!
Now we're even, you two-bit impostor.
Sealing Loki away broke the effects\nof his soulbinding.
Thank you, Harle. Because of you
Save the chat for later, Your Royalness.\nWe've got business to finish.
Tsk! He may not have fully recovered,\nbut it seems he can still move.
This new contract is amazing! I've never\nfelt such power from my Sigil before!
He's nowhere near as strong as before...\nWe can do this!
Yet his power remains tremendous.\nDon't let down your guard!
Give all you have so we can stop this\ntyrant's reign before it begins!
This time, I administer Her authority\nto save the entire world!
